It appears the connection between the JIRA Cloud instance and Bitbucket is being interrupted or torn down during the large attachment transfer. This causes the entire import to fail.

h3.Workaround
Export the repository directly to a file via Bitbucket import\export function. The archive will contain both the attachments and the JSON issue data export. Identify the largest attachments after extracting the archive and cross reference the JSON issue export using the attachment file names. You can then identify the specific issues in the repository that contain the large attachments. These can then either be deleted from the Bitbucket repository or downloaded and then deleted from the repository so that the import can proceed. The attachments can then be manually re-added to the corresponding imported JIRA issue.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Cloud*. Using *JIRA Server*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRASERVER-64774].
  {panel}

