If the comment's author is not specified, that means it is anonymous.  This is valid state and we should not lie and say that the importing admin is the person that wrote the text of the comment.

A similar problem exists when the user that wrote the comment does not exist (and is not specified to be created as part of the import).  Ideally, the comment should be created with that nonexistent user specified as the author, but this gets a little complicated in the 6.0+ world of userkey-username mapping.  I'd be happy if these got imported as anonymous instead of creating a new mapping for the nonexistent user so that we'll have the correct key to use for the mapping, but using the importing admin as the author is definitely wrong.
